114.1	Affirmative_action	Affirmative action	Affirmative action refers to policies that take factors including "race, color, religion, gender, sexual orientation or national origin" into consideration in order to benefit an underrepresented group, usually justified as countering the effects of a history of discrimination.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/18/Dahrendorf.jpg/220px-Dahrendorf.jpg
